    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>The memorialist nods, and in a gentle voice says, "A pilgrim must climb more than ridges, and cross more than plains."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>The memorialist shrugs. "You have paid me well, pilgrim, and my body has never complained of too much rest."</DefaultText>
